<br>
I lead the first successful raid to kill the Dragon on Gawaine. We did it with 105 people. I had done as much research as I could, but it was hard for me to tell fact from fiction until I got there. The plan I had come up with was executed to my satisfaction, but utterly failed. After the rez n rest, there were a million suggestions flying around, all based on all the facts and fictions that everyone hears. I forced alotta people to sit there and wait, while I conducted a few simple tests to figure out the Dragon Rules. I also tried another full on attack with some more rules that I thought would work, but was wiped again. The 3rd attack was the charm, we won. The rules I has set at the time was; anyone can do whatever they want, but only from under his belly. And if you were not going to enter the dragon lair, you must de-group and not be grouped with anyone. <br>
<br>
----------------------------------------<br>
Here are the FACTS about the dragon.<br>
<br>
Mr G Dragon IS a simple Caster class mob. If you start performing actions like attacking, healing, rezzing, from out of his melee range, he can decide to &quot;cast&quot; on the perpetrator of these actions, OR any of his group mates.<br>
<br>
His &quot;cast&quot; is a 350 or 400 radius AOE fire breath that no lvl 50 can ever survive if hit more then 2 times without heal. <br>
<br>
He has an extra ruleset that makes him &quot;cast&quot; on any toons (and their groupmates) that ever do any actions like attacking, healing, or rezzing from the outside of his lair. IE you can be very close to the dragon (in melee range), but if you rezz/heal someone from the inside of the lair, while you were standing on the outside of his lair, you have just doomed your entire group to AOE.<br>
<br>
At about 5% health, The dragon will auto-cast ; AOE stuns, and AOE teleports.<br>
<br>
If you DIE to his AOE-breath, and are rezzed, you are IMMUNE to his AOE-breath for approximtly 10 Minutes. (you will get a Mr G. attack you and you are hit for 0 damage message)<br>
-------------------------------<br>
<br>
Here are the rules that I believe any leader can easily win with. <br>
<br>
1) If you are not going to enter the dragon liar, de-group and do nothing during the entire raid. <br>
2) No Ice pets, ever.<br>
3) Anyone can attack, heal, and rez, however they want, but only from under its belly. If you get teleported away, do not do ANYTHING until you are back under its belly.<br>
--------------------------------<br>
<br>
Good luck to all servers!! Good luck to all Friars for respec stones!<br>
